<TITLE> Special cell for Bhola </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 21 (bdnews24.com)  The home ministry is going to open a special cell to observe law and order in Bhola before and after the by-elections scheduled on April 24. The law and order preservation cell will work between April 22 and April 25 at the Bhola-3 constituency. A home ministry circular disclosed this information on Thursday. Abdus Shobhan Shikder, home secretary, will act as the cell co-ordinator, the circular said. It will work under the guidance of the joint secretary of home ministry's political section. The special cell has been set up at room no 313 of the home ministry. Different information and complaints relating to law and order of Bhola-3 by-election will be received here. Information will be available to the public through phone (7168208). The cell will be manned by government officials round the clock. The initiative was taken to make the Bhola-3 (Lalmohan-Tozumoddin) by-election a success, the circular added. The inspector general of police, divisional commissioner of Barisal division, deputy commissioner of Bhola, police superintendent and other local administrators have been urged to provide the cell with all necessary information of the polling area. bdne
